headline: Home Depot (NYSE:HD) Names Angie Brown as New EVP and CIO
summary: Last month, Home Depot (NYSE:HD) named Angie Brown as Executive Vice President and Chief Information Officer, following a 27-year tenure with the company. Meanwhile, Home Depot's stock price rose by 3% over the month, coinciding with its announcement of first-quarter earnings showing a sales increase to $39.86 billion but a decline in net income. Despite the overall decline in the market driven by concerns over trade agreements, Home Depot's stock likely found support from its earnings...
